globalConfig.title: SSH Configuration
globalConfig.hostNameHelp:
URL that is used by SSH Client to connect to SCM-Manager (e.g.: ssh.hitchhiker.com:2222 or ssh://ssh.hitchhiker.com:2222).
If this is omitted, the host name of the base URL configured in global configuration will be used.
globalConfig.hostNameInvalid: Please specify a valid SSH client url (e.g.: ssh.hitchhiker.com:2222 or ssh://ssh.hitchhiker.com:2222)
globalConfig.portHelp: TCP port opened by SCM-Manager to provide SSH support
globalConfig.portInvalid: The port must be between 1 and 65535

ssh.description: May modify the ssh server configuration

*.displayName: Read ssh keys of all users
*.description: May read ssh public keys for all users

*.displayName: Read and set ssh keys of all users
*.description: May read and set ssh public keys for all users
